  "texts": [
    "For example, Veturi et al. (2024) use organizational data (e.g., policy documents) to enhance the performance of a frequently asked questions (FAQ) system.",
    "In principle, the data used for training an LLM (e.g., a text corpus from Wikipedia) could also be used for the nonparametric memory.",
    "In fact, most current user interfaces use some kind of RAG architecture to source the factual details of the original data.",
    "For example, an FAQ system (Veturi et al. 2024) will not only provide an answer to a specific question, but also a link to the corresponding document (e.g., a policy document).",
    "Since most organizations use LLMs from a vendor (e.g., from Microsoft), RAG can be used to add internal data and therefore contextual knowledge."
